website_summaries.verdict: A good alternative to dry kibble if you prefer to feed your dog canned dog food. Though pricey, dogs love it and owners love its quality ingredients.
pros: Premium canned food with chicken, vegetables, and brown rice
Balanced for puppies, adults, and senior dogs
Doesn't contain artificial colors or flavors
cons: Considering the recommended daily feeding amounts, making this a dog's primary diet can become costly, especially for owners of large dogs

customer_reviews.title: Rotten & bug infested food!!! Visible to naked eye!
customer_reviews.text: ABSOLUTELY HORRIFIC!!! This food was infested with bugs, and nasty rusted and corroded cans!! This was visible to the naked eye and they STILL SHIPPED IT!!! I’m absolutely disgusted. I would NEVER be able to feed my dog these incredibly disgusting cans!! I’m horrified someone would ship this!!
customer_reviews.author: Casey Reden

customer_reviews.title: No longer recommend
customer_reviews.text: I have ordered this product many times before. Usually, everything was fine. I like the product itself. Once in a while there would be a can or two in the case that was dented. I lived with it. But today, no longer will I live with it or order this product any more. Out of a case of 12, 9 cans were dented, most were really dented and a couple just a little. I expect more from my purchases. If I were in a store and saw a case of dog food in this condition, I would leave it on the shelf. I would not bring it home. I will not accept this kind of treatment from a company.
customer_reviews.author: CKM

customer_reviews.title: Shipping issue
customer_reviews.text: I like this product. I have shipping issue. Each of the cans in the order I received this month was bent. Two of the cans were punctured and dog food was oozing out. I do not eat from a product from a bent can, especially if it has been punctured - I do not feed it to my dogs either. So, I threw all of the cans in the trash. This past order was a complete waste of money.
customer_reviews.author: TNTinker

customer_reviews.title: Do not feed your dogs dented cans of dog food
customer_reviews.text: I have been feeding my dogs this food for years without a problem. In the last 3 months I have received order after order in which the package is all right but half to all cans are badly dented in. I will not feed my dogs food from smashed in cans. I have been able to get replacements but there is something wrong with quality control despite the last recent 2 unwelcome price raises,
customer_reviews.author: Long term customer

customer_reviews.title: Dog approved (no chicken!) + veggies/rice
customer_reviews.text: Our pup does well without chicken in her diet. Beef, liver, some vegetables - all in this can. Rated highly by dog-food-advisor online where they report on ingredients, ratios of fat and protein, as well as comment on extras/fillers often placed in pet food. Mixed with high quality kibble, this one hit the jackpot and created no tummy distress. Happy dog, happy family!
customer_reviews.author: KBTop Contributor: Pets

customer_reviews.title: My gangs favorite
customer_reviews.text: My gang loved this food! They would eat it without complaint. It was amazing to see them run to the bowls and lick them clean. It smells like dog food, and isn't covered with gravy. It's more of a moist food like pate. A big bonus is that it will slide cleanly out of the can without digging around. It will also cut cleanly for measuring and doling out over a couple of days. You can see bits of carrot in this food when you mix it with kibble. Unfortunately, one of my gang has recently been diagnosed with liver disease and can no longer eat this. I still highly recommend it to other people with finicky dogs.
customer_reviews.author: The Nutbarn Reviews

customer_reviews.title: Natural Balance Ultra Premium Wet Dog Food
customer_reviews.text: My pet likes his food, so no complaint with the product, however, the past two times I have ordered, some of the cans have been dented to the point of being very hard to open. I am sure this was done before the plastic seal was put in place. The arrival box from Amazon was in very good shape, so I know it didn't happen through shipping. Just so you are aware that some of your product has damaged cans. Thanks
customer_reviews.author: Karen J Lindell

customer_reviews.title: Not sure if this the real thing
customer_reviews.text: Not sure if this is the real product. I purchased 3 cases because it was a great price. Several cans were dented. Open up the cans and it has a different consistency from what I've bought in the past. What I received was a really soft, pate - type consistency. The product I bought from the pet store has a firm and drier consistency. My dog has been hesitant eating it this where as before he ate it with no problems.
customer_reviews.author: dominique hay

customer_reviews.title: Made my dog vomit
customer_reviews.text: If your dog is doing well with. His \ Her. Current dog food then stick with a winner.... This dog food made my dog sick... He vomited after eating this food. , gave him his regular food and he was fine. Tried this food one more time and again he vomited about. Thirty minutes after eating. That was it, I put the remainder of the cans in the trash.
customer_reviews.author: Karl

customer_reviews.title: Quality inconsistent, chemical smell
customer_reviews.text: My dog typically likes this food, but the last case I bought missed the mark. About one third of the cans emitted a chemical smell when opened. I thought it might be my imagination the first couple of times, but my dog refused to eat this food. Other cans smell normal, and my dog continues to eat the food in these. At this point, I’m just throwing out the ones with the weird smell. I’m not sure whether to chalk this up to one bad case of food and order again... May look for a different brand instead.
customer_reviews.author: C Smith

customer_reviews.title: Cans arrived dented
customer_reviews.text: It may be a unique experience, but 7 or the 12 cans arrived dented. They appeared ok from the top, but the sides were dented. My dog doesn't care for the food, but that might just be him assuming a dog's taste in food varies as much as a human's taste in food. Just looked at some of the other reviews and they suggest this was not a unique experience. Curious about what is going on with dents on the sides of the cans, but no denting on the tops of the cans. Can't seem to upload pictures, so cannot show the dented cans.
customer_reviews.author: C. L. Smith

customer_reviews.title: Good, but watch for dents.
customer_reviews.text: My boxer has no problem eating this dog food, however the biggest issue I have is all of the dented cans I receive. Something has to be done to protect the product when shipped. Perhaps it's the postal system. I refuse to give my dog any of the cans if they are deeply dented or worse. Great news is that Amazon stands by great customer service and replaced the damaged cans. DogFoodAdvisor.com gives the dog food 4 out of 5 stars which is a decent rating for a "pate consistency type" dog food.
customer_reviews.author: Steve

customer_reviews.title: Pup approved, vet approved, good value
customer_reviews.text: Pup approved, good value, good quality, no complaints from the vet. Only problem is that several cans arrive dented in each order, Amazon always replaced them, but I got tired of complaining about it.
customer_reviews.author: KJV

customer_reviews.title: They loved the taste
customer_reviews.text: I’ve never tried this brand before and I was scared my dogs wouldn’t like it. I was so surprised how quick they gulped it down. It was like they knew by the smell it was a different kind, and they wanted it NOW. They loved the taste, I am so happy I took a chance. I have already ordered another case for them. The only thing I did not like was that it had to be opened with a can opener, I prefer a pull top lid.
customer_reviews.author: Jill Hanson

customer_reviews.title: Finished buying this brand
customer_reviews.text: I've fed this to my dog for 7 years. I am receiving too many badly damaged cans in the cases from Amazon. Convenient getting it delivered but not practical (expensive) when you have to throw away a few cans from every case as they are so damaged. The consistency of the food is not always the same. It has been watery.
customer_reviews.author: Colleen S. Eklund

customer_reviews.title: Dog Food is great - Delivery is horrible
customer_reviews.text: I do not want to give the food a poor rating because my dog loves it and it has good ingredients but the last 2 deliveries have had cans dented and/or split open. It is too big of a hassle to pack it back up and return it if you do not discover the problem immediately. I will go back to purchasing from the pet store.
customer_reviews.author: Robert B.

customer_reviews.title: Miley (my schipperke) said this is one of her favorite dog foods
customer_reviews.text: Miley (my schipperke) said this is one of her favorite dog foods. She has epileptic seizures and I have to give her two pills/day. I put them in wet dog food and she gulps it right down! She likes all of the Natural Balance canned dog foods. Since she's so small (9# 4 oz), this size can rather than the full size is very practical. Glad this size is an option.
customer_reviews.author: nancyab

customer_reviews.title: Encouraged by veterinarians
customer_reviews.text: Second time to purchase from Amazon! Our sweet dog loves this food! When we read the ingredients and were encouraged by veterinarians to use it we had to try it. We have been told that it's great for dogs with allergy problems, itchy skin, and a sneezy respiratory system. It's encouraging to know it's rich in vitamins B6 and B12, which are needed for healthy metabolism and gastrointestinal function for our little senior dog. Thanks so much!
customer_reviews.author: Here

customer_reviews.title: Liver formula is great
customer_reviews.text: The rescue kennel had been feeding him Natural Balance dry, with some NB canned food mixed in. We tried different varieties and found that Tater Salad really loved the canned Liver Formula. He had gained 30 pounds after being rescued. Now he is a very healthy, muscley 71 pounds (gained 10 more pounds).
customer_reviews.author: Greg & Joyce

customer_reviews.title: The Perfect Recipe
customer_reviews.text: Don't Doggies deserve Good Tasting Food? I found the perfect recipe for my American Bulldog. Take 3/4 bowl of dry Dog Food. Add 1 tablespoon of Natural Balance . Fill with Cold Water than stir. My dog loves the combination of Broth, and Crunch. Wolfs it down every time. I tried microwaving and using hot water. She likes the crunch. BTW - Doesn't upset the stomach or give Diarrea
customer_reviews.author: Nicholas Winn

customer_reviews.title: My Dog Likes It
customer_reviews.text: Happy my dog likes this food. I use a tiny bit as a topper to mix into her kibble. Great value. The only downside is the can isn't an easy open with a pop top so I have to get my electric can opener out every time. Not a big deal but not convenient. Would definitely buy again though.
customer_reviews.author: BK3773

customer_reviews.title: Great quality ingredients & price. Dogs love
customer_reviews.text: Great value. Great food. My dogs love both the beef and liver flavors. Excellent quality ingredients and my dogs love the taste. Beef, beef broth and beef liver. Rice and carrots. Mehaden fish oil. Great quality and price! Even my pickiest dog loves it! I have just as many can of natural balance, as I do his Tiki Dog.
customer_reviews.author: Sara Meyers

customer_reviews.title: Dog loved it!
customer_reviews.text: My dog really loved this food! I got it for him after he had a tooth extracted and the other dog was extremely jealous that he wasn’t getting any hahaha! I was able to find this at a cheaper price at my local pet store though. The bigger can was close to the same price as the smaller can here.
customer_reviews.author: E. Davis

customer_reviews.title: the dogs haven't complained once...
customer_reviews.text: dogs love it. wanted to find something that is atypical as the pit bull has allergies to most typical things, this does the trick.
customer_reviews.author: yekkersrow

customer_reviews.title: Quality Dog Food
customer_reviews.text: My 13 year old dog just loves it. He's been on it for ten years. My two puppies decided they didn't want to eat their puppy chow so I put a teaspoon full of the wet food and mixed it up with their dry food and they ate the entire bowl full. Good product.
customer_reviews.author: Sharon

customer_reviews.title: as best practice). The Natural balance line affords the best ...
customer_reviews.text: If you have a dog, probably a Lab or Golden, who has had laryngeal tieback surgery, then you need a certain quality of canned food--healthy ingredients, pate texture, not too moist--to form into balls for the hand-feeding phasee (to which I have committed for the duration, as best practice). The Natural balance line affords the best choices in value, variety, and dog preference. I recommend the beef, chicken, and wild boar blends. My dog would underscore the latter. These would be fine for any dog, of course, but those whose dogs have had the procedure may welcome this recommendation.
customer_reviews.author: N. E. Julius

customer_reviews.title: What an amazing product! I've helped people with pet nutrition problems ...
customer_reviews.text: What an amazing product! I've helped people with pet nutrition problems over the years and this is one of my main recommendations. While I would like for it to be grain-free, I must say there is nothing at all this product lacks from the competitors out there. The most picky eaters that have been brought to my attention have loved this food. It provides a well balanced nutrition which immediately shows in the health of your pet's coat. I would recommend this product to everyone out there!
customer_reviews.author: obousonopr

customer_reviews.title: Best product for my chihuahua
customer_reviews.text: I bought these for my little and old dog, who generally doesn't like any dog food or she get bad diarrhea. I finally found something that she absolutely adores and doesn't make her sick! I also like that the meat is not in pieces so it is easy for her to eat without the risk of choking (she had 11 teeth removed). I just wish I didn't need a can opener to open them!
customer_reviews.author: Elisa

customer_reviews.title: Expensive, Smelly, gross pate...
customer_reviews.text: Wish i knew it was a “pate” type dog food before i ordered a case of this... My dogs don’t like it, I don’t like mixing it in with their dry food. Plus, not only is it expensive, it smells & looks disgusting....
customer_reviews.author: MerJames

customer_reviews.title: My dogs LOVE this one!
customer_reviews.text: It is liver, which I personally do not like. That does not matter, the "boys" do. They eat it up each time it is served! Thrilled to find something else they like.
customer_reviews.author: Valerie Shapiro

customer_reviews.title: FINALLY,  A DOG FOOD MY LITTLE GIRL LOVES!!
customer_reviews.text: I noticed many questions regarding whether this is pate or chunky pieces of meat in gravy. After trying several premium dog foods with the chunky pieces, I put faith in the raving reviews and decided to try this one. To my BIG surprise; my finicky, small breed dog loves this brand of pate only. She gobbles this up, leaving her plate spotless. Thanks Amazon for carrying this brand of dog food; I have not found it any stores that I frequently shop at.
customer_reviews.author: LOUIE

customer_reviews.title: I wanted to like this food and have tried it several times
customer_reviews.text: Steer clear of this Natural Balance food. I wanted to like this food and have tried it several times, but it keeps making my dog sick. Amazon has pulled various batches for days and weeks at a time but it keeps coming back. Amazon - you need to check the quality of this food. It makes my dog really sick nearly every other time I buy it. I don't mind spending good money on good dog food - but quality is important.
customer_reviews.author: Brandon Chomko

customer_reviews.title: My dog will only eat this food
customer_reviews.text: I've been purchasing 2 flats a month of this dog food for the past 8 months. My dog is very particular about his food and he likes this one. For a few shipments, some cans arrived dented but cans have arrived in much better condition on recent shipments. My dog continues to do very well on this food.
customer_reviews.author: V. Nott

customer_reviews.title: Sure enough I cut my finger real bad yesterday opening one of the cans
customer_reviews.text: Seriously who makes a non-self opening can at this day and age for puppy food. This is not a tomato can that you use every two weeks. This is puppy food you need to use twice a day or three times a day. So you need a can opener three times a day! Sure enough I cut my finger real bad yesterday opening one of the cans. Otherwise the product is very good and my dog loves it!
customer_reviews.author: Bora Ozturk

customer_reviews.title: A healthy dog food!
customer_reviews.text: This food, along with the beef flavor and liver flavor, immediately disappears when I serve it to my dog. She loves the food and the Vet tells me she is extremely healthy!!
customer_reviews.author: Lewander

customer_reviews.title: Picky Dog Loves This Dog Food
customer_reviews.text: My picky dog Tim Tim loves this God food. He turns his nose up to hard dog food but devours this in one sitting. I love that the ingredients aren't full of fillers and chemicals like other dog food brands. The price has gone up, that's why I gave it 4 stars instead of 5. Other than that - great product.
customer_reviews.author: The Lady Who Loves Dogs

customer_reviews.title: Dogs like, but wish liver was main ingredient, it’s not
customer_reviews.text: I have been buying this product for the last five years. It’s a great product, but I wish it had more liver than what is in the ingredient list., it has liver, but not as much as the name implys 🤔🙁
customer_reviews.author: SleepsWithDogs

customer_reviews.title: PUPPY LOVES IT!!!
customer_reviews.text: My golden retriever puppy would not eat much of his hard food. Since he is very young, we really wanted to encourage him to eat more for growth and so got this soft food to mix into his hard food. He gobbles it down, but it backfires b/c he just picks out the chunks of this. We finally found a hard food he loves, so now are giving this to him as an extra dinner treat. GOBBLES IT DOWN WHOLE!! He LOVES this stuff. All Natural Balance products are amazing. And this kept up the positive streak we've had with them. We even feed our cats natural balance brand food. NB hasn't let us down yet!
customer_reviews.author: For the love of books!!

customer_reviews.title: Great pricing on this product- no by-products or corn
customer_reviews.text: Really good price on this product. We were thrilled to find it on here, but unfortunately won't be purchasing again because our dog has allergies brought out by the food. Not the food's fault- it's high quality, no corn or by-products, but he might be allergic to the beef.
customer_reviews.author: S. SmithTop Contributor: Pets

customer_reviews.title: Our Miniature Schnauzer LOVES it!!!!
customer_reviews.text: When we first got our 1 year old rescue Schnauzer in August 2013, we started him on Paul Newman's Organic beef and he was very satisfied. (We also tried the PN dry, but he refused to eat it.) This past Dec. we could no longer find the PN beef on Amazon or in local stores. I contacted PN and they emailed that they were having difficulty finding organic beef. Bailey does not care for chicken or liver so I went to Dog Food Advisor.com and started searching 5 star canned dog foods. I discovered Natural Balance Beef and the Amazon price was right too. He LOVES it. He also LOVES the NB dry which we keep as an open feed.
customer_reviews.author: K. Chandler

customer_reviews.title: Love the size, dogs love the food
customer_reviews.text: My dogs love this, and I love the size - it's easy for me to use with regards to portions. I didn't know that a decent 6 oz size was out there. Also, this food is on the dogfoodadvisor.com as a 5 star food, so I also have the bonus of feeding my dogs a good meal. Yes, it is more expensive, but as they say - you get what you pay for, and I think this is worth it.
customer_reviews.author: EyesLiketheSea

customer_reviews.title: Great dog food!
customer_reviews.text: I have had a terrible time finding a dog food that works for 2 very different dogs...one makes one flake and have dry skin, the other makes the other one sick to the stomach, etc. I wanted to keep their food as high quality as I can to ensure good health - Natural Balance is the answer for us. I haven't had any issues with damaged cans at all. We switch them between different flavors - but liver always seems to be their favorite. We also give them. Love it and they've been on this for over 2 years now with great health!
customer_reviews.author: Denise

customer_reviews.title: Best price, dogs loved it
customer_reviews.text: We had to find a way to get our very elderly dog to eat. This helped get him interested in his bowl of kibble....we put about 4 tablespoons on top of the kibble, added water and probiotics, and down it goes! Best price here on Amazon Prime.
customer_reviews.author: Think Again

customer_reviews.title: 9 of 12 cans are dented Dog's getting sick
customer_reviews.text: 9 of the 12 can are all dented and both dogs are getting sick, my order before this case was fine and my dogs never got sick
customer_reviews.author: angela

customer_reviews.title: High Quality, Excellently Priced
customer_reviews.text: I rely on DogFoodAdvisor.com's food analysis and ratings. The Nature Balance Liver wet food scores 4.5 stars out of 5. Quality ingredients mean little to no gas for my dog - and the price cannot be beat! Highly recommend!
customer_reviews.author: Tom W.

customer_reviews.title: This is a great dog food
customer_reviews.text: This is a great dog food. The ingredients are trustworthy, and for someone like me who has difficulty with meaty products, the smell of this is not overpowering. It looks natural, and I have used this flavor as well as others and have never been disappointed.
customer_reviews.author: Dmp

customer_reviews.title: Dogs love and it is healthy
customer_reviews.text: My dogs normally eat the dry version as it is less expensive. But on the weekends they get these as a treat. They go crazy of this food.
customer_reviews.author: Michael G.

customer_reviews.title: Worth it.
customer_reviews.text: With our aging lab who has back issues we wanted to give her a dog food with ingredients we recognized. She has been the best dog ever so we treat her as such. It may be a little more expensive, but we feel good about giving it to her and she loves it. We have a rescue dog now who loves it too. We mix it with a high quality dry food and feel we are doing the best for both of them.
customer_reviews.author: LUVDVM

customer_reviews.title: Dog at 8/12
customer_reviews.text: Dog ate 8 very happily. Proceeded to turn his nose at the last 4 but ate them with a treat tossed in. The protein and ingredient list is impressive maybe some other flavor for my dog.
customer_reviews.author: Supergod7

customer_reviews.title: Smells weird. Like a smoked scent.
customer_reviews.text: Smells like they added a smoke flavoring to this. I'm not big into the added scents in dog food. My dog doesn't care. I think he'd prefer it smell like stinky liver!
customer_reviews.author: Ladybug

customer_reviews.title: No feed
customer_reviews.text: Not recommended. The Natural Balance Diet was recently declared by FDA that it can cause Heart Diseases in dogs. I had to stop feeding my dog right away although my dog liked it
customer_reviews.author: Mary

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: My dog has food allergies and I am so happy to have found this! It is not filled with water like some brands and you can actually see the rice, carrots and potatoes... (pull top would be much better, but small price for no allergies) She loves it! I have received a few batches that were dented but otherwise we are two very happy customers.
customer_reviews.author: Klynn

customer_reviews.title: This food made a difference in my dogs and the love it!
customer_reviews.text: I used to buy another brand of pet food until a coworker told me about Natural Balance and how his dogs lost weight and improved health wise. I love my dogs so much and with a referral like that, I promptly ordered it and my dogs absolutely love this food. They are so happy, healthier and my Vet told me that they already lost 10 pounds as compared to my old pet food that was loaded with fillers and stuff. It is obvious by just looking at this food when I serve it that the ingredients are better and natural. I am so glad my coworker told me about this food. I highly recommend it.
customer_reviews.author: Richie Rich

customer_reviews.title: Great for sensitive tummies!
customer_reviews.text: Great product! My dogs with their sensitive tummies and grain allergies luv this canned food and have no adverse reactions to it. There are chunks of white potato and carrots that my bassets just lap up! The mixture isn't too fatty and really has a good balance of protein and nutrients. My only complaint is when I purchase directly from the manufacturer the cans tend be dented quite a bit; so much so that I have difficulty opening the lid, but I have never had any issues with the food inside being spoiled, etc.
customer_reviews.author: OKCMomma

customer_reviews.title: DAMAGED CANS
customer_reviews.text: I USED THREE CASES OF THIS PRODUCT EVERY MONTH. IF YOU CAN'T DELIVER THE CANS (12) WITHOUT DENTS, YOU EAT THEM. DENTS LET AIR IN AND DIFFICULTY TO EXTRACT FOOD. DON'T DELIVER YOUR DENTED JUNK TO ME. IF AIR GETS IN THE FOOD ROTS.
customer_reviews.author: Patrick J. Frate

customer_reviews.title: No pop top/easy open lid....must use can opener!
customer_reviews.text: Food is good, but why no pop top/easy open lid on the 12 ounce cans? Unreal!! I won’t buy again simply for this reason.
customer_reviews.author: Suze KH

customer_reviews.title: Great Dog food
customer_reviews.text: When buying dog food, it's not about the taste for the dog, it's about the quality of the ingredients. This is a high quality dog food. I use it for my dachshund and my rat terrier. I have to keep the dachshund thin and this does the trick. Natural Balance was recommended by my vet for it's nutritional value and the dogs love it. Mix up what you feed your dogs. You will hear it's best to keep their diet consistent, but this is simply not true. In the wild, dogs would eat whatever they can, and it wouldn't be the same thing day after day and week after week.
customer_reviews.author: VRW

customer_reviews.title: Cans Cut Fingers!!!
customer_reviews.text: I have cut my fingers on these cans 3x and I have an electric can opener. During the process the opener occasionally stops. I'm upset about this.

customer_reviews.text: Good product but please put pull pop tab lids on the cans. Cans that require can openers is so 10 years ago

Both dogs love it.

customer_reviews.title: My dog isn't crazy about it.

The other thing I don't love is that I have to use a can opener on the can. I know that might sound picky, but most of your other premium foods have pop top lids, which is very convenient. I don't think I will be buying this again...
customer_reviews.author: Jaime Hayes

customer_reviews.title: Dogs love it!
customer_reviews.text: My dogs can be hard to please. I changed to this food a month ago, they love it. No more problems. It is an excellent price at Amazon, about 60 cents less then other pet stores.

customer_reviews.title: What I find interesting about getting this dog food is ...
customer_reviews.text: What I find interesting about getting this dog food is the fact that there are dented cans in the middle of the case and not just around the edge of the case. I wished there weren’t any. This has happened with each case we have received, even from different stores on Amazon, so it’s not an isolated incident. Doesn’t happen if I get it directly from Petco.

Diabetes specific wet food is expensive so we wanted a cheaper, but quality wet food for our non-diabetic dog. We first tried the Venison and sweet potato. My 9 year old LOVES it! BUT he wreaked after a few days. I mean his stinky breath was over bearing so next, we tried the lamb. Of course, he loved the lamb wet food. Big breath improvement but still couldn't accept kisses from the love bug. Finally, chicken. This was the last straw and thankfully we found t

customer_reviews.title: They like it but not as much as the beef formula
customer_reviews.text: I don't give my dogs the liver formula more than twice a week. They like it but not as much as the beef formula. Also, the consistency has changed and is a little more watery that the prior cans I purchased.

customer_reviews.title: Odd consistency and made puppies sick.
customer_reviews.text: First time trying. Food was odd consistency, very sticky and a tacky feel. Had to scrape it off spoon and fork. Puppies didn't seem to care for it and had diarrhea after eating for days. Discontinued feeding and threw it away.

product_meta.title: Natural Balance Ultra Premium Wet Dog Food with Real Meat & Brown Rice
product_meta.description:
Flavor Name:Chicken, Brown Rice, Carrots & Potatoes| Size:(12) 13 Oz. Cans

Our Ultra Premium Chicken Formula Canned Dog Formula provides your dog high-quality nutrition with a wholesome blend of premium chicken, grains, and vegetables. Formulated for all breeds and life stages from growing puppies to ever-energetic adult dogs, this diet helps support healthy digestion with no artificial flavors or colors.

Feeding Instructions

6 oz Can

Weight Adult Daily Feeding (Cans) Under 10 lbs 1 - 2 18 lbs 2 - 3 25 lbs 4 - 5 50 lbs 6 - 7 80 lbs 10 100 lbs 12 - 13 13 oz Can

Weight Adult Daily Feeding (Cans) Under 10 lbs 1/2 - 1 18 lbs 1 - 1 1/2 25 lbs 2 - 2 1/2 50 lbs 3 - 3 1/2 80 lbs 5 100 lbs 6 - 6 1/2 The amounts in the table are intended as guidelines only. The food intake should be adjusted according to the age, weight and activity of your dog. It is important for your dog's health to maintain a proper body weight. Consult a veterinarian for specific weight recommendations. Puppies, and Pregnant or Nursing Females, require 2 - 3 times the Adult amounts. A reduction in food intake is recommended for less active and older dogs. Serve at room temperature. Any unused portion should be covered and refrigerated. Fresh clean water should be available at all times!

Transition Instructions 'When switching your pet's diet, we recommend transitioning from the current diet to any new Natural Balance Formula over a 5 - 7 day period.

Day 1 - 2: 25% Natural Balance Formula, 75% Current Pet Formula Day 3 - 4: 50% Natural Balance Formula, 50% Current Pet Formula Day 5 - 6: 75% Natural Balance Formula, 25% Current Pet Formula Day 7: 100% Natural Balance Formula

If you do not have any of your current formula to mix, reduce the amount of formula fed for the first few days, feeding smaller more frequent meals over time. If your pet is more sensitive to change, please allow 10 - 14 days to fully transition onto the new formula.
